  "texts": [
    "Static AnalysisStatic analysis methods do not depend on running code on real hardware or a simulator.",
    "Instead, they focus on analyzing the task code directly, possibly with some annotations.",
    "By examining the set of possible control-flow paths within the task and integrating this with an abstract model of the hardware architecture, they can determine upper bounds for the combination [39].",
    "As discussed earlier, static analysis methods fall into two categories: deterministic and probabilistic.",
    "The following subsections provide a review of some studies within each of these categories."
  ],
